videos.description: Darrell Henderson started the day for Memphis with an 80-yard run from their own 10.
videos.headline: Henderson with a huge 80-yard run for Memphis

videos.description: Riley Ferguson gets Memphis on the board first with a two-yard touchdown to Joey Magnifico.
videos.headline: Ferguson finds Magnifico for the first Memphis TD

videos.description: Brandon Stephens gets UCLA into the red zone with a big 36-yard gain.
videos.headline: Stephens breaks out for a 36-yard run

videos.description: Jalen Starks rolls over a defender for UCLA's first touchdown of the day.
videos.headline: Starks pounds through for a UCLA TD

videos.description: UCLA lined up single file before a 3rd down snap that resulted in an incomplete pass.
videos.headline: UCLA fails to convert after strange I-formation

videos.description: Josh Rosen finds Jalen Starks for a long 50-yard play to get into the red zone.
videos.headline: Starks goes up for a 50-yard catch

videos.description: Josh Rosen rolls out and throws a five-yard touchdown to his tight end Jordan Wilson to increase UCLA's lead.
videos.headline: Rosen connects with Wilson for a short TD

videos.description: Riley Ferguson responds quickly with a 47-yard TD to Patrick Taylor Jr. cutting UCLA's lead to 17-13.
videos.headline: Memphis QB screen pass turns into long TD

videos.description: Riley Ferguson finds Tony Pollard for another screen pass resulting in a 42-yard touchdown to take the lead.
videos.headline: Ferguson throws another short screen for his 3rd TD

videos.description: Memphis' J.J. Russell has to be carted off after taking a big hit on a block during a kick return for UCLA.
videos.headline: J.J. Russell is carted off after taking big hit

videos.description: Josh Rosen takes it himself for a one-yard rushing touchdown to give UCLA the 24-20 lead.
videos.headline: Rosen gives UCLA the lead with a rushing TD

videos.description: Anthony Miller fully extends for a 41-yard catch over the middle from Riley Ferguson for a fantastic play.
videos.headline: Miller has an incredible diving catch for Memphis

videos.description: Anthony Miller follows up his great catch with a 33-yard touchdown reception from Riley Ferguson to take lead just before the half.
videos.headline: Ferguson throws a perfect TD to Miller  for the lead

videos.description: Mike Norvell know his team can't stop competing to keep pace with UCLA in the 2nd half.
videos.headline: Memphis head coach: Our guys gotta keep competing

videos.description: Riley Ferguson finishes the drive with a 12-yard touchdown to Anthony Miller who extends over the goal line to score.
videos.headline: Riley Ferguson throws for his 5th TD

videos.description: Josh Rosen throws a 65-yard pass for his 3rd total touchdown to Darren Andrews cutting the Memphis lead to 34-31.
videos.headline: Rosen finds an open Andrews for a long TD

videos.description: Tim Hart picks off Josh Rosen on a poor pass over the middle and takes it 60 yards to the house.
videos.headline: Rosen throws a pick-6

videos.description: Josh Rosen throws a 21-yard touchdown to Jordan Lasley bringing UCLA within 3.
videos.headline: Rosen connects with Lasley for his 4th TD

videos.description: Josh Rosen throws a 33-yard pass to Darren Andrews to get UCLA just outside the red zone.
videos.headline: Andrews beats his man over the middle for nice gain

videos.description: Josh Rosen finds Austin Roberts for a 22-yard touchdown to take the lead 45-41.
videos.headline: Rosen takes the lead with 5th TD

videos.description: Riley Ferguson answered back with a three-yard pass to Phil Mayhue to make it 48-45 Memphis.
videos.headline: Riley Ferguson takes back the lead with his 6th TD

videos.description: Josh Rosen throws his second interception of the day, this time to Terrell Carter who returns it 42 yards for Memphis.
videos.headline: Rosen intercepted in the red zone

videos.description: Memphis kicker Riley Patterson throws an interception in the end zone to Octavius Spencer on the fake field goal attempt late in the 4th quarter.
videos.headline: Memphis fake FG picked off by UCLA in end zone
